2\x80\x94is trending in the opposite direction. Of 10 US cities researchers identified as likely climate havens, all but one have seen the availability of affordable housing decrease in recent years, most faster than the national average:Read more about the effort to prepare cities for climate migrants\xe2\x80\x94and take a stab at designing your own climate haven\xe2\x80\x94in our Green Haven package, part of our Rethinking Cities obsession.Support Quartz journalism with our new referral program. You told us the Daily Brief makes you smarter, so why not share it with someone in your life who could use a knowledge boost? Start making referrals today to help us continue to keep you up to date every morning.Surprising discoveriesJust look at this stunning photo of a rare Siberian tiger. It won Sergey Gorshkov the title of Wildlife Photographer of the Year.These colors absolutely run. California officials have asked voters to stop disinfecting their mail-in ballots.A World War II bomb exploded in Poland. Divers had been trying to defuse it, and they were all unharmed.A designer created a \xe2\x80\x9cself-picking\xe2\x80\x9d guitar. Radiohead guitarist Ed O\xe2\x80\x99Brien is a fan.Stealing from Pompeii brings bad luck. At least according to a woman who sent back artifacts she took from the site 15 years ago.Oh you want some more? You\xe2\x80\x99re in luck! Our emails are made to shine in your inbox, sign up for one today.Latest Quartz India storiesTanishq is only the latest brand to face the ire of India\xe2\x80\x99s easily offended right wingQuartz IndiaAmazon and Flipkart are serving a new India during this year\xe2\x80\x99s festive salesQuartz IndiaWhat\xe2\x80\x99s at stake for India in the US presidential election?Quartz IndiaGovernment banks in India are abysmal when it comes to recovering money from defaultersQuartz IndiaWhy Indian Americans\xe2\x80\x94the wealthiest and most educated of US immigrants\xe2\x80\x94form a key voter baseQuartz IndiaConsumer confide